### **Interface TUN ogstun**

| sudo ip tuntap add name ogstun mode tun |
| --- |
| sudo ip addr add 10.45.0.1/16 dev ogstun |
| sudo ip addr add 2001:db8:cafe::1/48 dev ogstun |
| sudo ip link set ogstun up |
| ip addr show ogstun |

### **Persistance ogstun au reboot**

| sudo tee /etc/systemd/network/99-ogstun.netdev > /dev/null << 'EOF' |
| --- |
| [NetDev] |
| Name=ogstun |
| Kind=tun |
| EOF |
|  |
| sudo tee /etc/systemd/network/99-ogstun.network > /dev/null << 'EOF' |
| [Match] |
| Name=ogstun |
| [Address] |
| Address=10.45.0.1/16 |
| [Address] |
| Address=2001:db8:cafe::1/48 |
| EOF |

## **Etape 3/5 — HSS + MongoDB + abonne test IMSI=340041000088687**

### **Bloc 1 — MongoDB : cle GPG + depot + installation**

| curl -fsSL https://www.mongodb.org/static/pgp/server-7.0.asc \ |
| --- |
| │ gpg --dearmor \ |
| │ sudo tee /usr/share/keyrings/mongodb-server-7.0.gpg > /dev/null |
|  |
| echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/mongodb-server-7.0.gpg] \ |
| https://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu noble/mongodb-org/7.0 multiverse" \ |
| │ sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-7.0.list |
|  |
| sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y mongodb-org |

### **Bloc 2 — Demarrage MongoDB**

| sudo systemctl enable mongod && sudo systemctl start mongod |
| --- |
| sleep 2 |
| systemctl is-active mongod && echo 'OK' ││ echo 'FAIL' |

### **Bloc 3 — Demarrage HSS**

| sudo systemctl enable open5gs-hssd && sudo systemctl start open5gs-hssd |
| --- |
| sleep 2 |
| systemctl is-active open5gs-hssd && echo 'OK' ││ echo 'FAIL' |

### **Bloc 4 — Creation abonne test IMSI=340041000088687**

| # Remplacer Ki et OPc par les valeurs SIM reelles |
| --- |
| open5gs-dbctl add 340041000088687 PLACEHOLDER_KI PLACEHOLDER_OPC |

### **Bloc 5 — Parametres abonne APN/QoS**

| open5gs-dbctl update 340041000088687 \ |
| --- |
| --apn internet \ |
| --ambr-downlink 1000000000 \ |
| --ambr-uplink 1000000000 \ |
| --qos-index 9 \ |
| --arp-priority 8 |

### **Verification**

| systemctl is-active open5gs-hssd |
| --- |
| systemctl is-active mongod |
| open5gs-dbctl showfiltered 340041000088687 |
| sudo ss -tlnp │ grep 3868 │ column -t |

**Note : ***MongoDB est obligatoire pour Open5GS HSS/UDR — cohabite sans conflit avec PostgreSQL*

## **Etape 4/5 — Services systemd Open5GS : enable + start dans l****'****ordre**

| sudo systemctl enable mongod          && sudo systemctl start mongod |
| --- |
| systemctl is-active mongod          && echo 'OK' ││ echo 'FAIL' |
|  |
| sudo systemctl enable open5gs-hssd   && sudo systemctl start open5gs-hssd |
| systemctl is-active open5gs-hssd   && echo 'OK' ││ echo 'FAIL' |
|  |
| sudo systemctl enable open5gs-pcrfd  && sudo systemctl start open5gs-pcrfd |
| systemctl is-active open5gs-pcrfd  && echo 'OK' ││ echo 'FAIL' |
|  |
| sudo systemctl enable open5gs-sgwcd  && sudo systemctl start open5gs-sgwcd |
| systemctl is-active open5gs-sgwcd  && echo 'OK' ││ echo 'FAIL' |
|  |
| sudo systemctl enable open5gs-sgwud  && sudo systemctl start open5gs-sgwud |
| systemctl is-active open5gs-sgwud  && echo 'OK' ││ echo 'FAIL' |
|  |
| sudo systemctl enable open5gs-smfd   && sudo systemctl start open5gs-smfd |
| systemctl is-active open5gs-smfd   && echo 'OK' ││ echo 'FAIL' |
|  |
| sudo systemctl enable open5gs-upfd   && sudo systemctl start open5gs-upfd |
| systemctl is-active open5gs-upfd   && echo 'OK' ││ echo 'FAIL' |
|  |
| sudo systemctl enable open5gs-mmed   && sudo systemctl start open5gs-mmed |
| systemctl is-active open5gs-mmed   && echo 'OK' ││ echo 'FAIL' |

### **Verification globale**

| for svc in mongod open5gs-hssd open5gs-pcrfd open5gs-sgwcd \ |
| --- |
| open5gs-sgwud open5gs-smfd open5gs-upfd open5gs-mmed; do |
| state=$(systemctl is-active $svc) |
| enabled=$(systemctl is-enabled $svc 2>/dev/null) |
| printf '%-22s  actif=%-10s  enabled=%s\n' "$svc" "$state" "$enabled" |
| done |

### **Diagnostic si un service est en failed**

| sudo journalctl -u open5gs-NOM.service -n 30 --no-pager |
| --- |

## **Etape 5/5 — Verification ports + connectivite + readiness eNodeB**

### **Bloc 1 — Ports critiques**

| sudo ss -tlnpu │ grep -E '36412│2123│2152│3868│8805│2427' \ |
